Good evening TCSD Families,
We made it through our first day of distance learning. We wanted to thank all of our parents for your continued patience and support. We did experience some issues today as we expected we would. However, please remember each day we will get better, stronger and we will grow together. To our middle school students, please remember tomorrow will be periods 4, 5 & 6.

LOVE CHALLENGES, BE INTRIGUED BY MISTAKES, ENJOY EFFORT, AND KEEP ON LEARNING. – Carol Dweck

post_text:
Good Evening TCSD families,
We hope all is well with you and your family. As we continue to prepare for opening our schools in August, TCSD is in need of more specific info about your child/children. We are asking that all parents please complete our School Re-Opening Data Collection form ASAP (Click on Link:https://bit.ly/TCSDData). Paper copies are also available at our District Office which is located at 600 N Cherry. The information gathered from this form is extremely valuable to us for the re-opening of our schools. If you have already filled out and submitted the form, thank you. If you haven’t, please do so as soon as you can.
Thank you again for your patience and help with this process.

post_text:
Dear TCSD Parents & Students,

Since school sites are closed and you are learning from home, your teachers want to know how you are doing. This survey asks questions about what it is like learning from home. It will also ask questions about current learning activities with your teachers, learning activities with your classmates, and your feelings about learning from home. It does not ask for your personal info so your answers will be anonymous. Your student's answers will help schools in making future decisions, regarding learning from home. The survey is for students in grades 3rd-8th. Thank you for your participation, it is extremely important to us. Click the following link and find your school survey: https://www.tcsdk8.org/SAHSurvey/

You can also find a button on our website homepage labeled as '2020 Learning From Home Survey'

post_text: Last week, Wilson School hosted its 4th Annual AVID Showcase. Teachers and administrators from 8 districts and 10 schools in and outside of Tulare County came to hear about the positive impact that AVID has had at Wilson School. The attendees observed students, in TK - 5th-grade classrooms, learning through the use of AVID strategies. From organized binders and planners, focused note-taking, Philosophical Chairs, and collaborative and inquiry-based activities, attendees were able to observe engaging and rigorous learning taking place. Additionally, they were able to speak to children who were eager to share what they were doing in school. Many thanks to Wilson Principal John Pendleton and his teachers and students for another outstanding example of what it means to be an AVID school. AVID stands for Advancement Via Individual Determination, and Wilson students have the individual determination necessary to succeed! #ThisIsAVID

post_text: March's Youth Art Month kicks off Tulare City School District's art show season. We invite you and your family to come out to any and all of TCSD's student art exhibitions this spring. They are free to the public and light refreshments will be served. Each exhibition will showcase the creativity and talents of 3rd, 5th, 7th and 8th-grade students. Artwork mediums include acrylic paint, oil pastel, chalk, scratch art, colored pencil, graphite, and more. Each venue will house a different mixture of project styles, so come and enjoy them all.

post_text: Tulare City School District is now accepting applications for Mechanic. This is a 12 month, 8 hours a day position. Salary range is $19.63 to $23.54 per hour, plus applicable fringe benefits. Applicants must possess a valid and appropriate California Driver’s License, minimum Class B and Air Brake Endorsement; and produce a safe driving record per California Vehicle Code; A California School Bus Driver’s Certificate is desirable or must obtain a Certificate within one year. Previous bus driving experience is desirable. Four years of experience as a mechanic, including experience working with school buses, gas engines, hydraulic, electrical and air brakes systems required. Please submit applications to Tulare City School District no later than 4:30 PM on Wednesday, March 11, 2020. Please visit https://goo.gl/YAB7kL for details and application.

post_text: This year for our staff holiday card we decided to get our students involved. So, the 1st Annual Superintendent Holiday Card Design Contest was created. The contest was open to 4th-8th grade students. Out of the numerous entries that were submitted, two were selected to be used for our front and back cover. An Alpine Vista student’s design was chosen for the front and a Mulcahy student’s design was chosen for the back. We had a great time reviewing all of the artwork and we are so grateful for every student who took their time to submit an entry. Happy Holidays from all of us here at Tulare City School District!

post_text: A Lincoln Elementary student wanted to make a difference in her community during the holiday season. After making a call to the Lighthouse Rescue Mission she learned they were in need of cleaning supplies for family apartments. She organized a cleaning supply drive that generated over 100 items! What a shining example of how we can all make a positive difference in our community.

post_text: Amongst the many great submissions, we received for our 1st Annual Superintendent’s Holiday Card Contest one of them showcased our entire district’s school spirit in the design. A Los Tules student submitted his artwork, which incorporated all 15 of our schools. Our Superintendent was so impressed it was decided to take his original artwork as inspiration to design a poster that is being displayed at all of our schools. Congratulations!

post_text: HACER (Hispanic Alliance for Culture, Education & Recognition), a community service organization, which recognizes, promotes & enhances leadership development of youth in Tulare. One student from each of our middle schools was recognized at the December HACER Student of the Trimester Dinner. Thank you, HACER. Great job students!

post_text: Students in Mrs. Stewart's Home Studies/Independent Study Class with the help of our talented district art teachers created snowmen paintings and decorated cookies. The class also put together blessing bags which they donated to Tulare Emergency Aid to help members of our community. A special thank you to the Tucker Family who personally donated over 20 bags!

post_text: Nutrition Services hosted the first-ever Cornucopia of Flavors Food Show at Wilson Elementary on November 22nd. Students and parents had a blast taste testing 18 different items from 10 different suppliers! They got to try all sorts of new and exciting options and voted on what they would like to see on future menus. Check out the video to see how it went!

post_text: Tulare City School District is now accepting applications for Account Clerk (Technician). This is a 12 month per year, 260 day position. Salary range is $22.43-$27.54 per hour, plus applicable fringe benefits. Education and experience required: College coursework in accounting; knowledge of Word and Excel; two years experience in responsible financial and accounting work, preferably one year experience in school district business. Qualified applicants please submit applications to Tulare City School District no later than 4:30 PM on Thursday, December 19, 2019. Please visit https://goo.gl/YAB7kL for details and application.
